reviewText: THE GODTHUMB - is another of Steve Odekirk's (Bat Thumb, The Nutty Professor ) crazy and zany parodies using the thumb as the performers in this take-off of the Godfather films.Every major memorable scene from the original Scorsese Godfather film is parodied in the most hysterical way. From the horses head to the son who want to start a business to the other son who doesn't get along with anyone to the Hollywood producer who is not giving in to what the Italian Don wants.The Italian dialects are hysterical. This is a very creative, mini sets, costumes and hysterical music to accompany the absurd joke of a classic film and a timeless parody of obvious gags. The story is consistent and the gags very obvious.The DVD extras include the outtakes, which are funny and CAST interview with each of the thumbs. Chips film is clever, funny and extremely unique in style. The other films you should check out are the parodies of Star Wars called Thumb Wars, parody of Titanic called Thumbtanic and the parody of the Michael Keaton Batman called Batthumb.  See my reviews of each of them. This is extreme fun for the whole family. (12-9-02)
summary: Good, But Not The Best Of The Thumbs!

reviewText: The Godthumb(tm) while not the funniest of the series is still very good. A lot of the jokes are quick, and if you blink you'll miss them. Also the world that The Godthumb(tm) lives in is populated with not so intelligent thumbs, (many examples of this) and products,( such as: The Meat Cube Magican and Bagger Burger) so any thumb that is even remotely bright, shines brightly. If you liked Bat Thumb or FrankenThumb you'll most likely apperciate GodThumb(tm) and the jokes. The only complaint (if you can call it that) would be lack of commentary, which the other Thumb series seem to have (this may have since been rectified) While I enjoy the series, You might want to consider renting first before adding to your collection...but it's still a good story.
summary: sorta gets under your cuticle and sits there

reviewText: I love the Thumbnation concept, but unlike Thumb Wars this one just doesn't deliver humor for me.  It's attemps to spoof God Father are weak as there are hints and pieces of GodFather in here, but it's not very obvious.  If this movie was a concise spoof of just the 1st or all 3 God Fathers I would have had a blast but this was more like some rambling story with some characters influenced by God Father.  Even at it's fair price (considering it is a 30min movie maybe it isn't all that fair) I would have to say this isn't worth buying.
summary: Medicore humor that could easily be better
